posts.author: ruadh
posts.text:
The McAleese report is a massive, massive whitewash. filmstar-en is correct that it had no regard to the women's own accounts of their abuse during their incarceration there.
There's a very simple fact that proves this. When Ireland introduced a redress scheme for children who had been victims of abuse in residential institutions, among the institutions covered by the scheme were "teenage units" of the institutions that ran the laundries, like An Grianán at High Park, the site at which 133 bodies were found in unmarked graves in the 1990s. There is no dispute that (a) these girls were made work in the laundries or (b) they were abused while they were there: their redress was linked to the severity of the abuse. So, yes, the physical torture and abuse shown in the movie is absolutely true and indeed, a matter of public record.
Incidentally, the Irish government itself has recently began backtracking on McAleese: it's now claiming that there is no evidence of State liability in the running of the laundries, despite McAleese making clear findings that there was. (I really recommend that particular journalist's writings on the subject - he's the only one in Ireland that still seems interested.)
And no, they weren't all jails in the sense of women being physically unable to get out. But where would they go?

posts.title: Tây Ninh: Hàng chục người mất tiền vì hụi
posts.text:
07/11/2017 15:52 Tây Ninh: Hàng chục người mất tiền vì hụi TPO - Sau khi công bố vỡ hụi, công an xác định chủ hụi Nguyễn Thị Phượng tổ chức 13 dây hụi, chiếm đoạt gần 7 tỷ đồng của 57 người. Chủ hụi Nguyễn Thị Phượng tại phiên tòa phúc thẩm sáng 7/11. Ảnh: Tân Châu. Vỡ hụi 'khủng', cả xã nghèo nháo nhác 
Hôm nay 7/11, TAND Cấp cao tại TP.HCM xét xử và tuyên phạt Nguyễn Thị Phượng (SN1973, ngụ ấp Phước Thạnh, xã Phước Vinh, huyện Châu Thành, tỉnh Tây Ninh) 15 năm tù về tội “Lừa đảo chiếm đoạt tài sản”; buộc bị cáo Phượng hoàn trả số tiền hơn 3,3 tỷ đồng cho 31 bị hại. 
Trước đó vào ngày 14/12/2016, TAND tỉnh Tây Ninh xử sơ thẩm, tuyên phạt bị cáo Phượng 14 năm tù. Sau án sơ thẩm, các bị hại kháng cáo và Tòa cấp cao đã tăng án tù bị cáo vì nhận thấy có cơ sở tăng án. 
Theo nội dung bản án mà Tòa Cấp cao tại TP.HCM vừa tuyên, năm 2006, Nguyễn Thị Phượng bắt đầu làm chủ hụi và tổ chức nhiều dây hụi. Mỗi dây hụi có từ 21 đến 24 hụi viên tham gia và số tiền góp mỗi dây hụi từ 3 triệu đồng đến 10 triệu đồng/người/tháng. 
Đến năm 2013, lợi dụng việc các hụi viên tin tưởng, không đến khui hụi, Phượng ghi khống tên của các hụi viên bỏ phiếu hốt hụi, để lĩnh hụi nhưng không cho các hụi viên biết. 
Ngày 26/5/2016, đến lượt hốt hụi chót của nhiều hụi viên, Phượng tuyên bố vỡ hụi. 
Qua điều tra, công an xác định Phượng làm chủ 13 dây hụi, chiếm đoạt của 57 hụi viên với số tiền gần 7 tỷ đồng. 
Trong lúc nhà chức trách thụ lý vụ án, Phượng và gia đình đã hoàn trả gần 3,7 tỷ đồng cho 26 hụi viên, số còn lại không có khả năng chi trả. Tân Châu

posts.title: Ny seier for Zuccas Rangers
posts.text:
Seier: Rangers vant nattens kamp 5–3. Foto: Brad Penner / USA Today Sports / NTB Scanpix Vis mer Ishockey: Ny seier for Zuccas Rangers Opphentingen i den siste perioden sender Rangers et ytterligere steg opp fra bunnen på tabellen. 7. november 2017 kl. 4.09 Del på Facebook 
New York Rangers åpnet dårlig mot Columbus Blue Jackets, men en sterk siste periode sørget for 5-3 og lagets fjerde strake seier natt til tirsdag. 
Før 3. periode lå vertene under 1-2. Pavel Butsjnevitsj scoret sitt sjette mål for sesongen da han satte inn 4-3-målet snaut ti minutter før slutt. Da Blue Jackets jaktet på utligning på tampen, satte Michael Grabner inn 5-3. 
Før det hadde både Kevin Shattenkirk og Chris Kreider utlignet for Rangers. 
4-3-seieren er Rangers' fjerde strake seier. Mats Zuccarello noterte seg for én målgivende pasning i kampen – hans åttende for sesongen. Nordmannen fikk drøyt 21 minutter på isen. Så langt i høst har 30-åringen tre scoringer og åtte assists. Zucca og Rangers med tre strake seire Vendepunktet 
Første periode var målløs til tross for at hjemmelaget hadde et solid overtak. 38 sekunder ut i andre periode scoret gjestenes Artem Panarin. Fire minutter senere la Josh Anderson på til 2-0-ledelse. Grabner reduserte til 1–2 drøyt halvveis ut i perioden. 
Rangers utlignet til 2-2 i den tredje perioden, et mål Rangers svenske keeperlegende Henrik Lundqvist mener var vendepunktet i kampen. 
– Da fikk vi selvtillit og det ble vanskelig for Columbus å komme tilbake, sa Lundqvist som stanset 22 av 25 skudd mot Rangers mål. Kamp nummer 1000 
– Vi ville gjerne klatre på tabellen, men også lage en minneverdig kveld for «Nash», sa svensken etter kampen. 
Rangers-spiller Rick Nash spilte sin NHL-kamp nummer 1000 i oktober (mot Arizona), og ble hedret med en seremoni før kampen mot Columbus. 
Opphentingen i den siste perioden sender Rangers et ytterligere steg opp fra bunnen på tabellen etter en skrekkelig start på sesongen med det ene tapet etter det andre. Sesongen startet med ni tap på de tolv første kampene, men nå har Rangers vunnet fire strake. 
- Helt plutselig vinner man en kamp og får selvtillit, og da går det bedre. Vi har mer struktur i laget nå, og selv om vi fortsatt gjør en del feil kjennes det annerledes ut, sier Lundqvist. 
- Når man er lengst nede i kjelleren holder man fast på tanken om hvor fort ting kan snu. Man må ha troen på det man gjør, sier den svenske keeperkjempen. (NTB)

posts.text:
Juan Ignacio Pérez–Tabernero Sánchez ha sido galardonado con el tercer Premio Tauromaquia de Castilla y León 2017, un reconocimiento creado por la Consejería de Cultura y Turismo para distinguir la trayectoria profesional, los méritos, las actividades o las iniciativas de personas, entidades o instituciones que hayan contribuido a la promoción de la Tauromaquia en la Comunidad y hayan colaborado en la difusión de sus valores culturales. El jurado, reunido hoy en la sede de la Consejería de Cultura y Turismo, ha decidido conceder el Premio de Tauromaquia de Castilla y León, en su tercera edición, a Juan Ignacio Pérez–Tabernero Sánchez, titular de la ganadería Montalvo, queriendo reconocer al conjunto de ganaderos de reses bravas de la Comunidad, así como distinguir, en particular, la trayectoria profesional y los méritos de este ganadero que durante más de 30 años de profesión ha contribuido a la promoción de la Tauromaquia en Castilla y León. Para la concesión del premio, el jurado ha valorado la combinación de tres elementos: en primer lugar, Juan Ignacio Pérez-Tabernero es descendiente directo de una estirpe de ganaderos que se remonta a la ganadería fundada por su antepasado, Fernando Pérez-Tabernero, en 1884, en Salamanca, que contribuyeron de forma decisiva a cambiar la orientación productiva de la ganadería de lidia, desarrollando un modelo de ganadería moderna de reses bravas moderno que está obteniendo excelentes resultados; en segundo lugar, en este año 2017, se celebra el 50 aniversario del paso de esta ganadería a manos de su padre, quien se la traspasó al premiado en 1984 y, por último, es necesario resaltar la trayectoria de los toros de la ganadería Montalvo, que en los últimos años han lidiado en plazas importantes con éxito, varios han sido indultados y han obtenido hasta el momento en tres ocasiones, el Premio Toro de Oro. El jurado de este año del Premio Tauromaquia de Castilla y León ha estado presidido por el maestro salmantino Santiago Martín ‘El Viti’, I Premio Tauromaquia de Castilla y León en 2015, y han formado parte del mismo José Antonio Cabañeros, presidente de la Peña Taurina de León; María del Mar Gutiérrez, secretaria técnica de la Asociación Nacional de Organizadores de Espectáculos Taurinos (ANOET); María de la Peña Mónica Pérez, co-directora de la Cátedra de Estudios Interdisciplinarios en Tauromaquia de la Fundación General de la Universidad Salamanca; José Luis Lera, crítico y periodista taurino; Isabel Lorena de la Fuente, veterinaria taurina y miembro de la Junta Directiva de la Asociación de Veterinarios Especialistas Taurinos, (AVET); Luis Mata, presidente de la Peña Taurina de Burgos; Manuel Gutiérrez, inspector jefe Cuerpo Nacional de Policia y presidente delegado de la Autoridad de Plazas de Toros; Juan Diego Vicente, torero y presidente de la Unión de Toreros; Ana Pedrero, periodista y crítica taurina, y Julián Escudero, ganadero y veterinario de la Asociación de Ganaderías de Lidia. El premio, sin dotación económica, consiste en una escultura conmemorativa del escultor Venancio Blanco, cuya entrega se hará en un acto institucional, según recogen las bases del premio. Este reconocimiento pone de relieve el carácter de la Tauromaquia como un hecho singular de la Comunidad, que ha pervivido a lo largo de los siglos convirtiéndolo en un hecho patrimonial, social, cultural y económico de primer orden.

posts.title: SPDP Setnov Bocor, Fahri Kecewa!
posts.text:
Wakil Ketua DPR RI Fahri Hamzah mengaku kecewa dengan KPK karena surat perintah dimulainya penyidikan (SPDP) atas nama Setya Novanto "bocor" dan tersebar ke publik, padahal institusi tersebut harus bisa menjaga kerahasiaan surat tersebut.
"Karena KPK telah bertindak secara sembrono dengan membocorkan sprindik atau SPDP dan membocorkan rahasia-rahasia penyidikan," kata Fahri di Gedung Nusantara III, Jakarta, Selasa (6/11/2017).
Dia menilai seharusnya KPK lebih berhati-hati karena bagaimana pun DPR merupakan lembaga yang penting di Indonesia sehingga kalau Ketua DPR mau diperiksa, harus menggunakan etika.
Menurut dia, ada Ketetapan MPR Nomor No VI tahun 2001 tentang Etika Kehidupan Berbangsa, khususnya etika politik dan pemerintahan yang sering digunakan KPK namun tidak digunakan kepada Ketua DPR.
"Standar kita tentang cara kerja lembaga negara ini sidah dirusak oleh KPK. Pakai etika seharusnya, sebagaimana mereka menyembunyikan pemeriksaan terhadap banyak pejabat negara namun saya tidak mau menyebutkan namanya," ujarnya.
Menurut dia, tidak tepat status Novanto sebagai Pimpinan DPR yang masih dicekal berpergian ke luar negeri padahal proses praperadilannya menang.
Dia mengatakan apa yang dikatakannya bukan soal hanya terkait Novanto, namun siapapun Ketua DPR dirinya akan tetap mengatakan tindakan KPK itu telah merusak standar etika dalam bekerja di kelembagaan negara.
"Saya tetap mengatakan tindakan KPK ini memuakan karena ini merusak standar etika dalam bekerja kelembagaan negara," ujarnya.
Sebelumnya, sebuah surat yang diduga SPDP KPK terkait Setya Novanto tercatat dengan nomor B.619/23/11/2017 tertanggal 3 November 2017.
Sumber: SPDP Setnov Bocor, Fahri Kecewa

Meerdere gewonden nadat drone plots crasht in menigte Gisteren om 10:30 Mail 
In de Japanse stad Ogaki zijn zaterdag meerdere gewonden gevallen nadat een drone in een groep mensen crashte. Zes mensen, waaronder enkele kinderen, raakten gewond. 
De drone vloog zaterdag over de massa tijdens een beurs over robottechnologieën die in een van de stadsparken plaatsvond. Het onbemande luchtvaartuig van ongeveer vier kilogram strooide wat snoep over de mensen toen het plots veel hoogte begon te verliezen. Enkele seconden later kantelde het toestel en viel het hard naar beneden. 
In totaal waren er ongeveer 600 mensen aanwezig in het park. Zes van hen raakten bij de crash gewond. Hun leeftijden schommelen tussen 5 en 48 jaar oud. Gelukkig bleven hun verwondingen beperkt tot wat snijwonden aan het gezicht en de schouders door de propellers. 
De politie heeft de piloot van de drone reeds ondervraagd. Volgens de organisatie ging het om een 37-jarige man die in het bezit was van een vliegbrevet. Wat de crash precies heeft veroorzaakt, is nog onduidelijk.

Episode 10  The Package
Written by: Paul Zbyszewski and Graham Roland
Directed by: Paul Edwards
 with MIB/Locke's camp being watched by people using night vision goggles making the screen green and white. Sawyer walks to Kate who is sitting alone and hands her a mug.]
SAWYER : Want some cocoa?
KATE : Where'd you find cocoa?
SAWYER : I didn't, pretend.
[As the camp is scanned the sound of a camera taking pictures is heard in the background. Claire is sitting and holding a metal rasp. MIB/Locke is walking and twirling a branch as he approaches Jin who is changing the bandage on his wounded leg. The night vision stops being shown.
MIB/LOCKE : How's the leg?
JIN : Still hurts.
MIB/LOCKE : You should leave the bandage off for a while. The air'll do it some good.
JIN : I'll try that.
[Jin stops winding the bandage around his leg.]
MIB/LOCKE : You mind if I sit down?
[Jin looks at MIB/Locke and the seat.]
MIB/LOCKE : I know you and I haven't had time to talk but I was wondering if James had filled you in on what I showed him at the cliffs.
JIN : You mean the cave, the one with the names on the wall.
MIB/LOCKE : [nods] Most of the names have been crossed off now. There's just a few left.
[Claire moves nearer the campfire and overhears MIB/Locke's conversation with Jin.]
MIB/LOCKE : There are just a few left. "Kwon" is one of them.
JIN : Does that mean me or Sun?
MIB/LOCKE : [shakes head] Well, Jin, I'm not sure. What it does mean is the only way we can leave the island is if all the names that haven't been crossed off go together.
JIN : But Sun's not here.
MIB/LOCKE : [smiles] You just take care of that leg. I'm working' on it.
[MIB/Locke gets up and walks away. A partial time skip is heard and the scene switches to Sun sitting in the customs waiting area of the Los Angeles Airport. An agent escorts Jin to this area.]
CUSTOMS OFFICER : All right, Mr. Kwon, here's your suitcase and your watch.
MALE PA VOICE : Please proceed to the U.S. Customs Office.
[Sun takes her suitcase and walks to Jin.]
JIN : Money?
CUSTOMS OFFICER : I'm sorry. Federal Law says we have to confiscate your $25,000.
JIN : Confiscate?
CUSTOMS OFFICER : It means if you want it back, you're gonna have to fill out the necessary paperwork.
JIN : I, money?
CUSTOMS OFFICER : You can exit right over there, sir.
[The customs officer hands Jin his passport and walks away. Jin angrily grabs his suitcase and walks with Sun.]
JIN : [in Korean] Let's go.
SUN : [in Korean] Are you okay?
JIN : [scoffs] [in Korean] I've missed the meeting at the restaurant.
SUN : [in Korean] What was the money for?
JIN : [in Korean] I don't know. Your father gave it to me right before we left. He told me to deliver it with the watch. [pause] I don't ask your father questions. I do what he tells me.
[Jin and Sun look at each other. the front desk at a hotel. Sun approaches the desk clerk.]
DESK CLERK : May I help you?
[Sun hands him a piece of paper.]
SUN : Paik.
DESK CLERK : A reservation for Paik.
[The desk clerk checks for the reservation.]
DESK CLERK : Yes, I've got it right here. We've got a beautiful ocean view room for you on the eighth floor.
[He hands Sun a pass key.]
JIN : Two room, two, the eighth floor.
[Jin points to his left hand ring finger with no ring on it.]
JIN : No marry.
DESK CLERK : Oh.
JIN : Kwon. Jin Soo Kwon.
DESK CLERK : I'm sorry. I apologize. Yes, there is a separate room reservation for Kwon. [hands pass key] Room 842, here you go, sir. Miss Paik, Mr. Kwon, welcome to Los Angeles.
[Sun and Jin smile at the clerk then each other. A partial time skip is heard and the scene switches back to the island where Sayid is sitting on a log and chopping wood for the campfire.]
MIB/LOCKE : I'm leaving for a little while. I've got an errand to run.
SAYID : [stares blankly] When will you be back.
MIB/LOCKE : Morning. Keep an eye on the camp while I'm gone.
SAYID : I don't feel anything.
[MIB/Locke stops, turns around and addresses Sayid.]
MIB/LOCKE : Excuse me?
SAYID : Anger, happiness, pain, I don't feel it anymore.
MIB/LOCKE : Maybe that's best, Sayid. [pause] It'll help you get through what's comin'.
[MIB/Locke walks away. Jin sees this and quickly pulls his pant leg down then gets up and walks away. Sawyer notices and follows him.]
SAWYER : What are you doin', Hoss?
[Jin is filling a backpack.]
JIN : I'm getting out of here before that thing comes back.
SAWYER : What thing?
JIN : Locke. And you're just sitting around here listening to whatever he tells you.
[Jin starts to walk away and Sawyer grabs his arm to stop him.]
SAWYER : I ain't listenin' to nobody. I already told you I have a deal with Widmore so if you just calm...
JIN : It doesn't matter who you have a deal with. I've waited long enough. I'm going to find my wife.
[Jin walks away and Sawyer stops him again.]
SAWYER : Find her where?
JIN : I'll go back to the Temple and if she's not there, I'll try the beach [louder] but I will find Sun so stop trying to...
[Jin is hit in the chest with a dart. Sawyer is hit in the neck. He grabs his gun and is hit again. Darts are flying everywhere. Sawyer groans as he falls to the ground. Everyone at the camp is on alert. Two men with rifles look for the source of the darts and everyone runs to get out of the line of fire. Kate is hit in the back. There is confusion everywhere.]
KATE : Go! Uhh!
[Jin pulls out the dart and falls to the ground. Sayid is hit in the shoulder and Claire is hit in the neck.]
SAYID : Aah!
CLAIRE : Uhh!
[Everyone at the camp is on the ground unconscious as people walk among them wearing night vision goggles and are checking everyone. The group is Zoe, Seamus and other Widmore team members. Seamus takes off his goggles.]
SEAMUS : Is this the guy?
[They look at Jin lying on the ground semi-conscious.]
ZOE : Yeah, let's take him.
[Several men pick up Jin.]
LOST Logo
 beach camp where Frank and Miles are playing cards.]
MILES : Play your card, Captain.
[Frank checks his cards and throws one down. Ben is talking to Ilana as she cleans her rifle.]
BEN : Now what?
ILANA : We wait.
BEN : Wait [pause] for what?
[Sun is on the other side of the table from Ilana peeling mangoes and listening.]
ILANA : For Richard to come back.
BEN : You'll forgive my skepticism but the last thing Richard said before he went stomping off into the jungle was that we were all in hell and he had no idea what we were supposed to do next. In fact, I would bet money we never see him again.
[Jack walks to the table.]
ILANA : Hugo will find him. He will track him down and bring him back.
[Frank is putting down cards as Miles responds to the conversation.]
MILES : Unless Alpert's covered in bacon grease I'm not sure Hurley can track anything.
FRANK : Hey, don't talk about bacon.
ILANA : Jacob has never lied to me before. If he said Richard knows what to do then Richard knows what to do. He'll come back and until then we wait.
[Sun angrily throws mango onto the table and then the knife into the table and walks away. Jack watches Sun walk away. the garden Sun had once seeded and tended to. She pulls a plant out of the ground, shakes off the dirt, tosses it aside and goes for another. Jack approaches her.]
JACK : How are the tomatoes?
SUN : Dead.
[Sun turns from Jack and pulls out another plant.]
JACK : I remember when you first planted this here. Feels like a hundred years ago. You don't believe Alpert's coming back, do you?
SUN : I don't care if he comes back.
JACK : What about us [pause] being candidates?
SUN : What about it?
[Jack crouches down so he is eye level with Sun.]
JACK : Hurley took me to a lighthouse [pause] to Jacob's lighthouse. And [pause] there was a mirror and all around it there were [pause] there were hundreds of names written down.
SUN : I don't care. I don't care about Alpert or being a candidate.
JACK : Sun, there's a reason why we were brought...
SUN : [crying] I don't wanna hear about how this is our purpose or destiny! I just want you to go away and leave me alone.
[Jack nods, stands up and walks away. A partial time skip is heard and the scene switches to the hotel in Los Angeles. Jin is knocking on a door. Sun opens the door.]
SUN : [in Korean] Jin.
[Jin is holding the green leather box with the watch inside.]
SUN : [in Korean] What are you doing?
JIN : [in Korean] Your father sent me half way around the world to deliver the watch so I'm going to the restaurant.
SUN : [in Korean] Will you come inside? I don't want to have this conversation here.
[Jin looks around and enters Sun's room.]
SUN : [in Korean] It's eleven thirty. No one is going to be at the restaurant.
JIN : [in Korean] I should still try.
[Sun turns around and faces Jin.]
SUN : [in Korean] Jin, this man works for my father. It's not going to be a problem.
JIN : [in Korean] What do you care? You're here for a shopping trip.
SUN : [in Korean] So that's all you think of me? That I'm here to shop?
JIN : [in Korean] No.
[Sun unbuttons the top button on her sweater.]
SUN : [in Korean] Maybe you should tell me to button it like you did on the plane?
JIN : [in Korean] It was a crowded flight. I didn't know who might be watching us.
SUN : [in Korean] [chuckles] No one is watching us. So, do you want me to button it?
JIN : [pauses] [in Korean] No.
[Sun unbuttons the next button and slowly walks closer to Jin.]
SUN : [in Korean] What about...
[Sun unbuttons her sweater to reveal her bra and breasts. She continues to unbutton the sweater.]
SUN : [in Korean] this one?
JIN : [in Korean] No.
[Sun continues to unbutton the sweater and pulls it back to reveal her torso.]
SUN : [in Korea] And this one?
JIN : [in Korean] No, definitely not that one.
[Sun takes off her sweater and tosses it aside. Jin tosses the watch case on the bed and takes Sun in his arms and kisses her. As they lay back on the bed, a partial time skip is heard and the scene switches back to the island where Sun is still pulling plants out of the ground when she cuts her hand on a spiky frond. As she tends her wound, someone approaches.]
MIB/LOCKE : Sun.
[Sun turns and sees MIB/Locke and quickly stands up.]
MIB/LOCKE : I'm sorry. I didn't mean to startle you.
[Sun is standing next to a red leafed plant and says nothing.]
MIB/LOCKE : Bad Day?
SUN : What are you doing here?
MIB/LOCKE : [smiles] I found your husband.
SUN : What?
MIB/LOCKE : I promised you I would reunite you two. Took me a little longer than I thought it would but he's with my people back at my camp across the island.
[MIB/Locke puts out his hand to Sun.]
MIB/LOCKE : I can take you to him right now.
SUN : I don't believe you. You killed those people at the Temple.
MIB/LOCKE : Those people were confused. They were lied to. I didn't want to hurt them. Any one of them could've chosen to come with me and I'm giving you that choice, Sun, right now. I would never make you do anything against your will. I'm asking you.
[MIB/Locke reaches his hand out again to Sun.]
MIB/LOCKE : Please, come with me. Jin is waiting.
[Sun looks at MIB/Locke, thinks, looks at his outstretched hand then turns and runs away.]
MIB/LOCKE : Sun!
[He runs after her. She turns her head every few moments to see where he is.]
MIB/LOCKE : Sun, wait!
[Sun continues to run through the foliage with MIB/Locke not far behind. She turns to check him and when she turns back to runs into a tree hitting her head. A partial time skip is heard and the scene switches back to the hotel where Sun is lying on a bed and is slowly opening her eyes. As she rolls over, Jin is sitting bare chested with his back against the headboard. They lie in the afterglow of lovemaking.]
SUN : [in Korean] I've got an idea.
JIN : [in Korean] What's that?
SUN : [in Korean] Let's run away.
JIN : [in Korean] What?
SUN : [in Korean] I'm serious. Let's run away.
JIN : [in Korean] How could we do that?
SUN : [in Korean] I've got an account
[Jin gets out of bed.]
JIN : [in Korean] This was your plan all along?
[Sun kneels up on the bed.]
SUN : [ [laughs] [in Korean] Are you angry?
JIN : [in Korean] No, but what you're saying [pause] it's forbidden.
SUN : [in Korean] Do you want to be with me or not?
JIN : [in Korean] Of course I do, I love you.
SUN : [in Korean] Good. [pause] Then there's something you need to know.
[Jin nods. There is a knock at the door.]
JIN : [In Korean] Who's that?
SUN : [in Korean] I don't know. I put out the sign.
[Sun puts on her robe and Jin walks with her.]
JIN : [in Korean] [whispers] Tell them you're sleeping.
[Jin goes into the bathroom. Sun straightens her hair out in front of a mirror and then takes a long look in it. There is another knock on the door. She answers the door.]
KEAMY : Ms. Paik, hi. I'm, uh, Martin Keamy. I'm a friend of your father's.
[Sun just looks at him and says nothing.]
KEAMY : [looks in] Mind if I come in? I believe you got something for me. Hmm?
[Keamy enters Sun's room. A partial time skip is heard and the scene switches back to the island. Sun is lying on the ground, unconscious, next to the tree she ran into. Ben sees her and checks on her.]
BEN : Sun? Sun, can you hear me?
[He helps her sit up. She is regaining consciousness.]
BEN : What happened?
[Sun grabs her forehead.]
BEN : You all right?
SUN : [in Korean] Where is he?
BEN : I'm sorry, what?
SUN : [in Korean] He was chasing me. He was here. I saw him, he was...
BEN : Slow down, tell me what happened in English. Who did this to you?
SUN : Locke.
 MIB/Locke returning to his campsite. The campfire is smoldering and everyone is lying on the ground unconscious. Surprised, he looks around, locates Sayid, removes the dart and turns him over.]
MIB/LOCKE : Sayid! Sayid! Hey!
[MIB/Locke shakes Sayid trying to get him to wake up. Sayid slowly opens his eyes.]
MIB/LOCKE : What happened?
SAYID : We were attacked.
MIB/LOCKE : By whom?
SAYID : I don't know.
MIB/LOCKE : [upset] Where is Jin?
[Sayid is still groggy. large open room with metal walls. Jin is sitting in a chair in the middle of the silent room, unrestrained. As he awakens he looks around trying to gain his bearings. There are wires and speakers on walls surrounding this chair in the middle of the room. He gets up and walks to the door to find it is locked.]
JIN : Hey! [bangs on door] Hey!
[No one responds to his banging on the door. He sees a box with a lever and pulls the lever. The room darkens and a video plays. It flashes pictures quickly with techo music audio. Jin covers his ears.]
THINK ABOUT YOUR LIFE Pictures quickly changing like fractals We are the causes of our own suffering Picture of the swirly top of an eco-friendly light bulb The moon One eye Two eyes A Buddha Wood burning stove EVERYTHING CHANGES Musical keyboards
[Jin manages to push the lever up and stop the video and the room returns to normal. He walks a bit and is addressed by someone behind him.]
ZOE : Wow, that was weird, huh?
JIN : Where am I?
ZOE : It's called Room 23. The Dharma Initiative was doing experiments on subliminal messaging in here but you know all about the Dharma Initiative, don't you Mr. Kwon?
JIN : Why did you bring me here?
ZOE : Relax, you're safe.
JIN : I'm leaving.
[Zoe puts a stun gun to Jin's back and the electrical shock forces Jin to the floor.]
ZOE : Sorry, but we went through a lot of trouble getting you here off the other island and I can't let you leave.
[Jin is still trying to recover from the stun gun's effects.]
JIN : What do you want from me?
[Zoe opens a large map.]
ZOE : These are grid maps that, that the Dharma people used to identify pockets of electromagnetism. Whoever signed this could really help me out. Uh, I know, I know the writing's difficult to read but, but it sure looks like it says, "Jin-Soo Kwon." So is it you or isn't it?
JIN : You want answers to your questions then get me your boss. I want to talk with Charles Widmore.
ZOE : Well, then, you're in luck, Mr. Kwon, because he'd like to talk to you, too.
[ big island and MIB/Locke's campsite. MIB/Locke is loading a gun and speaking to Sayid.]
MIB/LOCKE : You a good swimmer?
SAYID : Good enough.
[He hands Sayid the gun.]
MIB/LOCKE : Wrap this in plastic, you don't want it to get wet. We're taking the outrigger.
[Claire is watching MIB/Locke closely.]
MIB/LOCKE : Something wrong, Claire?
[Claire looks around then walks over to MIB/Locke.]
CLAIRE : Um, what, what you said to Jin [pause] about the names on the wall [pause] you told him you needed them all to get off the island.
MIB/LOCKE : Yes, I did.
CLAIRE : So, was, um, was my name on the wall?
MIB/LOCKE : No.
CLAIRE : Well, then it doesn't matter if I get on that plane, then, I mean, you don't need me.
MIB/LOCKE : No, that's not true, Claire. I need you.
[MIB/Locke takes Claire's hand and has her sit next to him.]
MIB/LOCKE : And there's plenty of room on that plane for all of us.
CLAIRE : Well, when we go home, Aaron's not gonna know me, stranger to my own son. He thinks Kate's his mother.
[MIB/Locke exhales and looks over at Kate sitting next to the fire.]
CLAIRE : Is her name on the wall?
MIB/LOCKE : No, Claire, it isn't, not anymore but I need Kate.
CLAIRE : Why?
MIB/LOCKE : Because I'm three people shy of getting off this island and Kate can help me get these people on that plane. But, once she does, whatever happens, happens.
[MIB/Locke zips his backpack, gets up and walks away from Claire.
SAWYER : What's up with the guns? You two going somewhere?
MIB/LOCKE : We're taking a boat ride over to the other island.
SAWYER : What do you need a boat for? Can't you just turn into smoke and fly your ass over the water?
MIB/LOCKE : Do you think if I could do that I would still be on this island?
SAWYER : No, 'cause that'd be ridiculous. What the hell you going over there for, anyway? I thought you were trying to avoid Charlie Widmore.
MIB/LOCKE : They took one of our people, James so I'm going to get 'em back.
[Sawyer watches intently at MIB/Locke and Sayid as they walk away. The scene switches back to Keamy and Sun in her hotel room. She picks up the green leather box with the watch. She notices Jin's shoes and pushes them under the bed with her foot. She hands Keamy the box.]
KEAMY : Oh, this for me?
[He opens it and looks at the watch.]
KEAMY : Uh, this is really nice. [chuckles] Your bodyguard is supposed to give me some money. Where's Mr. Kwon.
SUN : No English.
KEAMY : Hmm?
[There is a knock at the door.]
KEAMY : All right, uh, sit down.
[Keamy answers the door and let's Omar into the room.]
OMAR : I checked his room. He's not there.
[Keamy puts the watch box on a table and notices a glass of champagne.]
KEAMY : Check the bathroom.
[Omar opens the door and finds Jin in his boxers.]
OMAR : Come on, let's go.
[Keamy puts on the watch.]
KEAMY : Mr. Kwon, why don't you come and join us? [loudly] Look, thank you for the watch, okay? But you're also supposed to give me an envelope with money in it, $25,000. Yeah?
[Keamy rubs his fingers together.]
JIN : [to Sun] [in Korean] What can we do?
SUN : [in Korean] We'll give them some of our money.
JIN : [in Korean] You want us to pay him?
KEAMY : [babbles] Stop that. I feel like I'm in a damn Godzilla movie. [to Omar] What's that guy's name? The, um, the Russian guy, he speaks like nine different languages, uh, uh Danny's friend.
OMAR : Mikhail.
KEAMY : Mikhail. Can he speak Korean?
OMAR : I think so.
KEAMY : Okay, go get him.
[Omar leaves the room.]
KEAMY : Now put your damn clothes on.
 a seating area in the room. Mikhail has joined them. Omar stands by the window.]
SUN : [in Korean] The money was confiscated at customs but I have money.
MIKHAIL : She says the money her father gave them was taken at customs.
KEAMY : Mm, that's not my problem.
SUN : [in Korean] Let us go to the bank and I'll give it to you.
MIKHAIL : She wants you to let them please go to the bank. They will get it for you.
KEAMY : [inhales/exhales deeply] You take her to the bank. I'll take Casanova here to the restaurant and we'll meet there.
MIKHAIL : [in Korean] He'll take Jin to the restaurant.
JIN : [in Korean] Please, you must promise not to tell Mr. Paik about us. Please.
KEAMY : What's he whining about?
MIKHAIL : He wants you to promise that you won't tell her father that they are involved.
KEAMY : Oh, hey, don't worry about that. Okay? Your secret is safe with me. Okay? Just bring me the money and we can all live happily ever after, right?
[Mikhail smirks and takes Sun to the bank. A partial time skip is heard and the scene switches back to the beach camp on the island where Jack is checking the wound on Sun's head. Ilana rolls her eyes at Ben and turns away.]
BEN : What? Oh for the fourth time, I was gathering mangoes and she was already unconscious when I found her. Why won't you believe me?
ILANA : Because you're speaking.
JACK : You got a pretty decent sized bump, might be a slight concussion. You can understand what I'm saying.
[Sun nods.]
JACK : But you can only speak Korean.
SUN : [in Korean] That's right.
MILES : She hits her head and forgets English? Are we supposed to buy that?
FRANK : Asked the man who communes with the dead.
JACK : It might be aphasia. It's, um, a condition that's caused by trauma and it affects the language center of your brain but it's usually temporary. Sun, you're gonna be okay.
[Ilana sees Richard and smiles.]
MILES : What are you smiling about?
[Ben turns then everyone looks and sees Richard and Hurley.]
RICHARD : Pack your bags, we're leaving.
 MIB/Locke getting out of the outrigger on Hydra Island. He walks up to a row of pylons and stops. Three bullets hit the sand next to his feet. Seamus and his team come out of the foliage with their rifles aimed at MIB/Locke.]
SEAMUS : Don't move! Let me see your hands!
[MIB/Locke raises his hands and wiggles his fingers.]
MIB/LOCKE : Easy, friend. I come in peace.
[MIB/Locke walks along the row of pylons. Seamus and the team walk on their side of the pylons with their rifles still aimed at MIB/Locke. Charles Widmore meets MIB/Locke.]
WIDMORE : Do you know who I am?
MIB/LOCKE : Charles Widmore. Do you know who I am?
WIDMORE : Obviously, you're not John Locke. Everything else I know is a combination of myth, ghost stories and jungle noises in the night.
MIB/LOCKE : I think you know more than that judging by these [pause] pylons.
WIDMORE : Why did you come here?
MIB/LOCKE : You took one of my people, Jin Kwon.
WIDMORE : I have no idea what you're talking about.
MIB/LOCKE : [pause] A wise man once said that war was coming to this island. I think it just got here.
[ beach camp. Richard grabs a backpack from a table and starts filling it up. Jack follows him.]
JACK : Where exactly are we going, Richard?
[Bens joins Jack and Richard.]
RICHARD : [to Ben] Where's Locke?
BEN : What?
RICHARD : You said he came to recruit you. Where did he say he'd be?
BEN : Hydra Island.
RICHARD : [to Frank] Which is exactly where you landed the plane that you flew back here, right?
FRANK : That's right.
RICHARD : This [pause] man wants to leave the island and that plane's the only way he can do it. You wanna know where we're going? We're gonna stop him.
MILES : [to Hurley] This is your fault, isn't it?
HURLEY : Sort of.
ILANA : How are we gonna stop him from getting on that plane?
RICHARD : We have to destroy it.
SUN : [in Korean] What? You want to destroy the plane? How are we supposed to get off the island?
RICHARD : Why isn't she speaking English?
JACK : She was hit on the head when she was running away from Locke.
RICHARD : He came back here?
[Jack nods. Richard walks over to Sun.]
RICHARD : What, what did he want? What did he say to you? You, you understand me?
SUN : [in Korean] Yes, I understand you idiot but if you think I'm going to help you destroy our only way off this island you're insane! I cam here to find my husband so I could bring him home, not so I could save the damn world! [points to Ilana] She says I'm important. If that's true, you need me! So understand this, I'm not going anywhere!
HURLEY : I don't think she wants to come.
[Sun briskly walks away from the beach camp. A partial time skip is heard and the scene switches to the bank in Los Angeles. Sun is at the counter with Mikhail. A teller is assisting them.]
SUN : [in Korean] Is there a problem?
MIKHAIL : Ms. Paik would like to know if there is a problem.
FEMALE BANK TELLER : I'm sorry. I'm showing that your account was closed. The balance is zero.
[Mikhail smiles.]
MIKHAIL : [in Korean] She says your account is closed.
SUN : [in Korean] No, that can't be right. No one knows it exists but me.
MIKHAIL : If she may ask, who closed the account, please?
FEMALE BANK TELLER : Looks like her father. Mr. Woo-Jung Paik had access. The funds were transferred to one of his other accounts at our main branch in Seoul.
MIKHAIL : [in Korean] Your father closed the account.
SUN : [in Korean] Why [pause] would he do that?
MIKHAIL : [in Korean] Why do you think?
[Sun is left speechless. The scene changes to the kitchen in the restaurant. Omar drags Jin into the walk-in refrigerator.]
OMAR : Uhh! Get in here.
[Omar grabs a chair and brings it with him into the refrigerator and makes Jin sit on it.]
OMAR : Let's get in. Come on, Get in.
KEAMY : What's going on?
OMAR : I bumped his head on the door.
KEAMY : Oh come on, Omar. You gotta be more careful than that.
[Omar starts to wrap Jin's wrists with duct tape as Keamy wets a cloth and brings it back to Jin.]
KEAMY : I got this. You go get the Arab guy.
OMAR : Hey, I'm an Arab.
KEAMY : Just go pick him up.
[Omar leaves and Keamy takes the duct tape and dabs the cut on Jin's forehead.]
KEAMY : Sorry about that. Omar's loyal but he lacks attention to detail. You really don't understand a word I'm saying to you right now, do you? Nothin'? All right, just hold still, okay?
[Keamy continues to wrap duct tape around Jin's wrists.]
KEAMY : I'm gonna strap you in here just in case you figure out what's about to happen to ya. I can't have you freaking out.
[Keamy pats Jin on the shoulder and sits down.]
KEAMY : I don't think you realize how unhappy Mr. Paik was when he found out that you were doing his little girl. Well, you know, that twenty five grand that you were supposed to deliver, that was my fee for popping you. From what I hear, you know, anyone who works for Paik knows the cardinal rule, hands off the boss' daughter. But you, you couldn't resist her, could you?
[Keamy taps Jin's chest.]
KEAMY : The heart wants what the heart wants.
JIN : Thank you.
[Keamy scoffs then tapes Jin's mouth.]
KEAMY : I'm sorry. Some people just aren't meant to be together.
[Keamy closes the refrigerator door. the Hydra. Widmore briskly walks to Zoe.]
WIDMORE : What the hell were you thinking?
ZOE : I'm sorry, I know, I know we panicked.
WIDMORE : This was not supposed to happen for days. We had a time table.
[Jin stands by the door listening.]
ZOE : See, he was leaving their camp.
WIDMORE : Well, you should have let him leave and get him in the jungle.
ZOE : Well, maybe you should put a mercenary in charge instead of a geophysicist.
[Zoe notices Jin and Widmore turns to look. He turns back to Zoe.]
WIDMORE : [deep exhale] What's done is done. I need you to get the package from the submarine and take it to the infirmary. Can you do that for me please, Zoe?
ZOE : Yeah, sure.
[Zoe turns and leaves the room. Widmore signals for the armed man at the door to leave.]
WIDMORE : Mr. Kwon, my deepest apologies for everything that's been done to you. My name is...
JIN : [interrupts] I know who you are. Why did you bring me here?
WIDMORE : We searched the Ajira plane, discovered your wife's luggage and found this inside.
[Widmore hands a camera to Jin.]
WIDMORE : I thought you might want to have it. Go ahead, turn it on.
[Jin turns on the camera and looks at the stored photographs as Widmore steps back and leans against a desk. The first picture is of Ji-Yeon in a red jumper and white blouse. She is about 3 years old. Jin smiles.]
WIDMORE : Her name is Ji-Yeon. The next picture she is in a blue dress and is with the family Shar Pei.]
WIDMORE : Your daughter.
[The next picture is Sun, Ji-Yeon and the Shar Pei. Jin holds back tears.]
WIDMORE : I understand you've never seen her before.
[The next two pictures are at a birthday part for Ji-Yeon. The next is a picture of Ji-Yeon wearing a pink sweater.]
WIDMORE : I have a daughter too. I now what it's like to be kept apart. I understand the one thing you want is to be reunited with your wife and daughter but it would be short lived if that thing masquerading as John Locke ever got off this island. Your wife, your daughter, my daughter, everyone we know and love [pause] would simply cease to be. I came here to make sure that doesn't happen.
JIN : How?
WIDMORE : Come with me. I think it's time for you to see the package.
JIN : What package?
WIDMORE : It's not a what. [pause] It's a who.
[ restaurant. "Caution Keep Door Closed" is on the front of the refrigerator. Jin is still in there. He hears a conversation taking place outside in the kitchen.]
SAYID : Did you put my brother in the hospital?
KEAMY : That's a dangerous world, Sayid, and you know that because you're from Iraq.
[Jin turns and sees a razor next to the duct tape on a chromed, wire shelf. He tries to move the chair to reach for it.]
KEAMY : You never know when somebody's just gonna sneak up...
[Jin is startled by the sound of a gunshot. Another gunshot is heard accompanied but the thud of a body hitting the floor.]
KEAMY : All right? Your brother doesn't owe me anything. The debt's forgiven.
[Another gunshot is heard followed by the thud of another body falling to the floor. Jin starts kicking the metal door to the refrigerator. Suddenly the door opens. Sayid is standing outside the door with his gun aimed at Jin. As he enters the refrigerator, still aiming his gun, Jin sits up and back. Sayid rips the duct tape from Jin's mouth.]
JIN : [in Korean] Please don't kill me. Please let me go.
SAYID : Who are you?
JIN : No English.
SAYID : I don't know why you're here and I don't really care.
[Sayid tosses the duct tape on the floor and exits the refrigerator.]
JIN : No! Free!
[Jin looks to the razor next to the duct tape.]
JIN : Free! Free!
[Sayid sees the razor and the tape. He looks around, takes the razor from the shelf, opens it and places it in Jin's bound hands.]
SAYID : Good luck.
[Jin starts to cut the duct tape holding him in the chair. Mikhail enters the kitchen of the restaurant with Sun. He doesn't see or hear anything and takes out his gun. As he turns a corner he sees Omar, another man and Keamy on the floor. Sun is startled. He rolls Keamy over.]
MIKHAIL : Martin? Martin? Who did this to you?
KEAMY : Look behind you, you idiot.
[Jin is standing behind Mikhail with a gun on the back of his head. He stands up.]
JIN : [in Korean] Drop your gun!
MIKHAIL : [in Korean] Take it easy. It's okay. Who did all of this?
JIN : I said put the gun down. Now! Sun, move away. [to Mikhail] Did you hear me? Drop it or I'm going to kill you!
MIKHAIL : No, I don't think so because if you were the person who did this you would've shot me already.
[Mikhail turns around quickly and disarms Jin. Jin reacts quickly and holds Mikhail's arm away from himself by using martial arts. The guns fires twice before Jin can get Mikhail's arm down on the table. He pushes his right elbow into Mikhail's face, spins around and grabs the gun from the table as Mikhail picks up a knife and turns to Jin. He is greeted by two bullets to his right eye. Sun is sitting on the floor crying. Jin puts the gun in his waistband and runs over to Sun.]
JIN : [in Korean] Sun! Oh my God! Oh my God!
[Sun has been shot and is bleeding profusely from her abdomen.]
JIN : [in Korean] I'm going to get you some help!
[Sun is hysterical and in shock. Jin picks her up in her arms and walks out of the kitchen.]
SUN : [in Korean] I'm pregnant.
[As they leave the kitchen area the scene switches back to the island. Sun is sitting on the beach by a small fire. Nighttime has arrived. Jack walks to her and sits on the sand.]
JACK : I brought you a couple of things. I was thinking about a patient I had during my residency. Car crash, banged his head. When he woke up he couldn't talk. The guy was frustrated; I mean [chuckles] who wouldn't be. And then one of the nurses said, "Just because he can't speak doesn't mean he can't write.
[Jack unzips his backpack and takes out a pen and pad that he gives to Sun.]
JACK : Think you could give it a try?
[Sun takes the pan and pen. She writes, "Yes" on the pad and shows it to Jack.]
JACK : It'll take a little longer to get your point across but at least you have your voice back. [pause] I went back out to your garden to see if he was there. He wasn't but I found this.
[Jack takes a cloth out of his backpack then removes the contents to show one small red tomato.]
JACK : That's one stubborn tomato. [smiles] Guess no one told it, it was supposed to die.
[Sun writes, "Sorry" with a sad face next to it then shows it to Jack.]
JACK : Don't worry about it. You're not the first person to tell me to leave them alone.
[Sun and Jack chuckle.]
JACK : Locke, what did he say to you?
[Sun writes, "He said he has Jin."]
JACK : Why didn't you go with him?
[Sun writes, "I don't trust him."]
JACK : Do you trust me?
[Sun looks at Jack and nods. Jack nods in return.]
JACK : Sun, come with us and I'll help you find Jin. I'll help you find him and I'll get both of you on that plane and as far away from this island as you can get.
[Sun smiles as she holds back tears.]
JACK : I promise.
[Sun looks down and sees Jack's outstretched hand and takes it. The scene switches back to MIB/Smokey's campsite. Kate is still sitting alone by the fire as Sawyer sits down next to her.]
SAWYER : Where'd you go?
KATE : What?
SAWYER : Looked like your brain took a little stroll.
KATE : Why aren't you worried, James.
SAWYER : I am worried. Just really good at pretending I ain't. But I got a feeling this is almost over 'cause if Locke rode over there on the boat with Sayid, then Charlie Widmore blew him right out of the water.
KATE : And what if he didn't?
SAWYER : Well, then we're screwed six ways from Sun...
Kate, Sawyer and the rest of the camp look and see MIB/Locke returning from his errand.]
SAWYER : Oh, Hell!
KATE : He's alone.
[Sawyer gets up and walks to MIB/Locke.]
SAWYER : Thought you went over there to find Jin.
MIB/LOCKE : They said they didn't have him.
SAWYER : And you believed that.
MIB/LOCKE : No.
SAWYER : Where's Sayid? Did you lose him, too?
MIB/LOCKE : When you were over there, James, you mentioned Widmore has someone guarding a room on the submarine, guarding something that he didn't want you to see.
SAWYER : Yeah, so?
MIB/LOCKE : I don't like secrets.
[MIB/Locke walks away from Sawyer. pier on Hydra Island where the submarine is docked. Sayid's head pops out of the water as he slowly swims to the pier. Zoe and two men are trying to get someone out of the submarine.]
ZOE : Okay, come on, okay. Hey, be careful with him. All right, okay.
[Sayid quietly approaches the pier.]
SEAMUS : The guy can hardly stand.
ZOE : Well, what do you expect? Oh, oh, will you watch!
[As they stumble along they drop the man they are trying to transport. His shoulders and head hang over the side of the pier. It is a partially conscious Desmond. He looks down at Sayid in the water as Sayid looks up at him. Desmond is trying to get his eyes to focus properly.]
SEAMUS : How much did you give him?
ZOE : Obviously, I gave him too much but we needed him knocked out for the trip. I'm not a nurse. Come on, get him up.
SEAMUS : Let's go, Mr. Hume.
ZOE : Be careful.
SEAMUS : Come on.
[Sayid watches as the two men and Zoe take Desmond along the pier.]
LOST logo
END

취업사이트 조사에 따르면 4대 ‘신입사원 병’으로 안구건조증, 손목터널증후군,
치핵 그리고 ‘스트레스성 위염’을 꼽았습니다.
신입생만의 문제가 아닌 직장생활을 하고 있는 이들 모두에게 적용되는 질환이 아닐까합니다.
그중에서도 스트레스성 위염은 치열한 경쟁 속에 살고 우리는
눈 깜짝할 사이에 먹어 치우는 식사 습관과 맵고 짠
자극적인 음식의 반복된 섭취로 위장 건강에 악영향을 미치고 있습니다.
이처럼 잘못된 식습관으로 인해서 현대인들은 위산과다로 속 쓰림,
가슴통증, 목 이물감 등 증상을 경험하게 되는데,
이는 위염과 역류성식도염의 대표적인 증상입니다.
대부분 이와 같은 증상을 쉽고 빠르게 해결하기 위해서
PPI(양성자펌프억제제) 또는 제산제를 복용하는 일이 잦은데,
초기에는 증상완화 효과를 얻을지 모르지만 장기간 반복된 복용은 위산 분비를 감소 시킬 뿐 아니라
철분과 마그네슘의 흡수를 방해해 미네랄 불균형을 유발하게 됩니다.
때문에 현대인들은 소화 장애와 함께 ‘미네랄 불균형’이 심각한 수준에 있습니다.
미네랄은 인체를 구성하는 원소로
신체의 각종 대사 작용을 관여하는 중요한 기능하는데,
미네랄 불균형 현상은 피로도 증가· 스트레스 수치 상승· 소화계 호르몬 분비에도 영향을 미쳐
위산과다 혹은 소화 장애의 악순환으로 이어지게 됩니다.
이에 약복용이 장기간으로 이어질 경우 약을 멀리하고
‘위염에 좋은 음식’을 찾는 이유라 할 수 있습니다.
하지만 대부분이 위염에 좋은 음식은
일정시간의 조리와 휴대성이 좋지 않은 이유로 꾸준한 섭취가 쉽지 않습니다.
이와 반대로 미네랄알칼리수 닥터M은 다량의 미네랄 함유와 500ml로
하루 3병 15일의 꾸준한 복용한 결과
위염에 좋은 변화를 얻을 수 있다는 연구 결과로 증명되었습니다.
미네랄은 인체를 구성하는 4%이지만 하나의 성분이 아닌
칼륨· 칼슘· 마그네슘· 요오드· 나트륨· 구리· 철 등 원소들을 말합니다.
체내에 합성이 안 돼 식품으로 섭취해야 합니다.
닥터M에는 화학적인 합성에 의해 생성되는 미네랄이 아닌,
자연 상태에서 얻어지는 칼슘과 마그네슘이 기존에 마시던 물과 달리
월등히 높게 함유되어 있어 체내 미네랄 밸런스를 맞추도록 도와주는 기능을 합니다.

posts.title: Q. 공전무 카페 이용방법
posts.text:
어떤 분이 공전무 카페 이용방법에 대해서 쪽지를 남기셔서 답글을 써봅니다.
Q1. 공전무 카페 이용하려면 교재 구입은 무조건 다 구입해야 되나요?
 - 전 공전무 카페는 인강만 듣고 교재는 구입하지 않았습니다.
 - 기본교재는 무크랜드라는 사이트에서 구매해서 그 쪽 강의를 우선 듣고,
 - 무크랜드 인강이 별로인 경우에만 공전무 카페의 인강을 들었습니다.
 - 무크랜드, 공전무 둘 중 뭐가 낫다고 할 수 없을 만큼
 각 사이트마다 저한테 맞는 인강과목이 달랐습니다.
 하지만, 어쨋든 기본 교재는 구입해야 하지 않을까요?
Q2. 공전무 교재는 매년 바뀌나요?
 - 제 경험상 교재는 매년 바뀝니다.
 - 특히 공전무의 경우 교수님들이 매년 바뀌고
 바뀐 교수님의 경우 가르치는 교재가 바뀔 가능성이 높습니다.
 - 하지만, 1차 과목은 교재는 바뀌어도 내용은 크게 변하지 않으니 중고책을 구입하셔도 될 수 있습니다.
 - 그래도 법 종류 공부가 처음이라면 들으시는 인강에 해당하는 새 교재를 사는 것도 좋을 수 있습니다.
Q3. 동영상 화질이나 이용에 불편함은 없나요?
 - 네 없습니다.
 - 유튜브로 듣는 경우 1.25와 1.5배속으로도 들을 수 있고,
 - 아예 유튜브 동영상을 다운받아서 들어도 되고,
 - 어쩌면 별도 어플을 쓰거나, 해당 사이트들어가서 인강을 들어야 하는 무크랜드 보다 편했습니다.
Q4. 교재비 16만원 외의 추가비용은 발생되지 않나요?
 - 처음 질문에 대한 답변에 썼듯이 저는 공전무에서 교재 구입하지 않아서 잘 모르겠습니다.
그럼 즐공, 열공하시길 바랍니다

posts.author: Blog Admin (noreply@blogger.com)
posts.title: YYY - A Tribute to The Beach Boys' Pet Sounds (2017)
posts.text:
FACEBOOK: https://www.facebook.com/therealyyy/ 
Written by Raymond Burris, posted by blog admin 
YYY’s A Tribute to The Beach Boys’ Pet Sounds sets a new standard for releases of this stripe. Tribute albums aren’t nearly as common as they once were and it is difficult to recall a single instance of a musical performer who debuted with one. Austin Carson, otherwise known as YYY, isn’t your typical performer however. Minneapolis based Carson has an all-encompassing musical vision that irrepressibly imposes itself on the iconic album’s fourteen songs and he further augments the effort by putting a cadre of local indie musicians and singers to work in guest star roles throughout the release. The production is very good and, despite the predominance of electronic textures in these reinterpretations, Carson calls upon a wide variety of instruments to help realize this album. One cannot accuse Carson of aiming low with his object of veneration. YYY tackles, with this release, one of the most imposing reputations in pop music and succeeds spectacularly invoking its grandeur in a different voice for a new generation. 
There’s an overall mix to the album of YYY following the template laid down by the original song and appending his own inventions within that structure, but there are likewise moments scattered across this release where he literally refashions Brian Wilson’s ideas towards different ends and imbues them with a distinctly different musical character. “Wouldn’t It Be Nice?”, the album opener, reveals another side to his approach – his wont for dissembling the album’s standards like this song. Anyone familiar with the original will find much to admire here, especially his singing and construction of the harmony parts, but there’s much here that goes far beyond Wilson’s vision for the music. He makes liberal use of guest performers on the album so the songs where YYY takes the lead and doesn’t make use of others talents are particularly notable. “That’s Not Me” has an immensely charismatic vocal and one of the aforementioned arrangements that does a nifty balancing act between retaining faithfulness to Wilson and Asher’s original while still remolding the song towards YYY’s own ends. The only other song on the album where YYY chooses to go it alone is the wildly inventive take on “Let’s Go Away for a While”. 
None of the above should be construed to mean his presence isn’t strong in the remaining songs. It’s omnipresent, but unstintingly willing and ready to accommodate other’s talents. He finds particularly sympathetic collaborators in Al Church, Matthew Jon, and vocalist Devata Daun. Church’s contributions to “Sloop John B” help YYY capture every bit of the wide-eyed soulfulness we hear in the original while still translating it into Carson’s unique musical language. His guitar contributions to the finale “Good Vibrations” are, along with the vocal arrangement, key to the success of that performance. Matthew Jon assisted YYY with the superb mix powering the album as a whole, but his musical talents are felt most strongly in the album’s version of the outright pop standard “God Only Knows”. No amount of familiarity with this song will prepare you for how well Jon and Carson acquit themselves with this. Devata Daun proves to be a world class partner on YYY’s interpretation of “I Just Wasn’t Made for These Times” and highlights one of the album’s poorly hidden strengths – the presence of female vocalists. It gives a fresh coat of paint to already sparkling works of vibrant color. A Tribute to The Beach Boys’ Pet Sounds is everything that an album like that should be and more – it makes a clear personal and artistic statement about its driving force.

Moyes opnieuw aan de slag in Premier League Vandaag om 10:26 Mail 
Premier League-club West Ham United heeft een dag na het ontslag van de Kroaat Slaven Bilic zijn nieuwe hoofdcoach beet. De Schot David Moyes, ex-coach van Everton en Manchester United, neemt het roer over. Volgens Engelse media zou Moyes een contract tekenen voor 2,5 seizoen, met de optie aan het einde van het seizoen de overeenkomst te verbreken. 
De 54-jarige Moyes heeft een boel ervaring in de Premier League. Tussen 2002 en 2013 leidde Moyes Everton, waarna hij door Manchester United in de zomer van 2013 werd gecontracteerd als opvolger van Sir Alex Ferguson. De erfenis van Ferguson bleek echter te zwaar om dragen en in april 2014 kreeg Moyes, nog voor het einde van een eerste tegenvallend seizoen, de bons. Een seizoen bij Real Sociedad (2014-2015) en een mislukt gevecht tegen de degradatie bij Sunderland (2016-2017) later, krijgt hij een nieuwe kans in de Premier League. Moyes nam vorig seizoen ontslag bij Sunderland nadat die club degradeerde. Sindsdien was de Schot werkloos. Foto: AFP 
West Ham kende een beroerde start dit seizoen en staat na elf wedstrijden pas op de achttiende plaats in de Premier League, een degradatieplaats. De Hammers tellen voorlopig slechts negen punten. Het team telt met Cheikhou Kouyaté (ex-Anderlecht, Brussels en Kortrijk) een oude bekende van de Jupiler Pro League in de rangen. 
Moyes wordt in Engeland aanzien als de ontdekker van Rode Duivel Marouane Fellaini. De Schot plukte de middenvelder eind augustus 2008 voor een toenmalig recordbedrag weg bij Standard en nam hem nadien ook mee naar Manchester United.

posts.text:
Moyes opnieuw aan de slag in Premier League Vandaag om 10:26 Mail 
Premier League-club West Ham United heeft een dag na het ontslag van de Kroaat Slaven Bilic zijn nieuwe hoofdcoach beet. De Schot David Moyes, ex-coach van Everton en Manchester United, neemt het roer over. Volgens Engelse media zou Moyes een contract tekenen voor 2,5 seizoen, met de optie aan het einde van het seizoen de overeenkomst te verbreken. 
De 54-jarige Moyes heeft een boel ervaring in de Premier League. Tussen 2002 en 2013 leidde Moyes Everton, waarna hij door Manchester United in de zomer van 2013 werd gecontracteerd als opvolger van Sir Alex Ferguson. De erfenis van Ferguson bleek echter te zwaar om dragen en in april 2014 kreeg Moyes, nog voor het einde van een eerste tegenvallend seizoen, de bons. Een seizoen bij Real Sociedad (2014-2015) en een mislukt gevecht tegen de degradatie bij Sunderland (2016-2017) later, krijgt hij een nieuwe kans in de Premier League. Moyes nam vorig seizoen ontslag bij Sunderland nadat die club degradeerde. Sindsdien was de Schot werkloos. Foto: AFP 
West Ham kende een beroerde start dit seizoen en staat na elf wedstrijden pas op de achttiende plaats in de Premier League, een degradatieplaats. De Hammers tellen voorlopig slechts negen punten. Het team telt met Cheikhou Kouyaté (ex-Anderlecht, Brussels en Kortrijk) een oude bekende van de Jupiler Pro League in de rangen. 
Moyes wordt in Engeland aanzien als de ontdekker van Rode Duivel Marouane Fellaini. De Schot plukte de middenvelder eind augustus 2008 voor een toenmalig recordbedrag weg bij Standard en nam hem nadien ook mee naar Manchester United.
